          "date": "2021-01-07 13:17:44.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-14055 obdclass: fill hole in struct obd_device",
        "message": "LU-14055 obdclass: fill hole in struct obd_device\n\nPerformance testing showed a significant performance reduction from\nadding the obd_debugfs_vars pointer field near the end of struct\nobd_device.  This reduced client IOR performance by 45%, though the\nspecific cause is unknown.  Adding and removing only the one field\nshowed that it was directly the cause of the performance regression.\n\nRearrange a few fields in struct obd_device to fill two 4-byte holes\nand avoid the increase in structure size caused by the new pointer.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I0bc1d915943034e2eac62b67ee1c8a29583ebbe5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
